Rating: 3
Nothing that's going to blow your mind, but it was a nice change of pace, and a better accompaniment to the Filipino London Broil also on this site than plain rice would have been. One thing I felt was that the method was overly complex, so next time, I'll just cook my rice as usual (simmered 20 minutes on the stove) and just pour the vinegar mixture over. I've eaten rice almost daily for over 20 years, and don't see a noticeable difference between regular rice preparation and this odd rinse-soak-simmer-boil-rest method.

